                  <msItem>
                     <p> CAMBRIDGE (Hospital of St. John the Evangelist). <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Gosefeld</surname>, master of
                  the <orgName key="org_100008">Hosp. St. John  Evang .</orgName>
                        </persName>, and the brethren of <orgName key="org_100008">the same</orgName>
                        <!-- not in VIAF -->, in consideration of the
                        charity, &amp;c., moving <persName><forename>John</forename>, bishop of <placeName key="place_100022" type="diocese" role="bishop">Ely</placeName></persName>, in allowing the hospital to elect
                  their own master so often as a vacancy occurs, agree that he and his successors
                  shall participate in all their prayers, &amp;c., for ever, and that they will
                  offer at the shrine of St. Etheldreda a wax candle of three pounds weight - in case
                  of default distraint to be made upon their lands or possessions, or upon the
                  rectory of <placeName key="place_100044" role="rectory">Hornyngestrete</placeName>. Dated 13 Jan., <origDate when="1332">1332</origDate>. . </p>
                  </msItem>
